==English==

===Etymology===
From [[package]] + [[management]] + [[system]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#{{italbrac|computing}} The tool used by an [[operating system]] ([[OS]]) to [[administrate]] [[addition]], [[removal]] and [[upgrade]] of [[software]] [[application]]s.  Examples of '''package management systems''' on different OSs are: Linux: RPM; Solaris: pkgadd; HP-UX: SD-UX; Debian: apt-get; Win32: Visual Installer

